<TEXT>
this year nasa conducted its first agencywide study of 
maintenance so it could better distribute building repair funds to 
the eight major field centers and their subsidiaries 
nasa teams visited 14 sites all but the smallest installations 
were included in the threemonth survey which was completed in 
june 
the results are as follows with the first being the center with 
the most maintenance problems included with each listing are the 
centers location average building age and function 
1 michoud assembly facility new orleans average building age 
is 346 years this subsidiary to marshall space flight center 
builds external tanks for the space shuttle 
2 marshall space flight center huntsville ala 325 years 
provides the shuttle engines external tanks and solid rocket 
boosters and manages spacelab missions and development of space 
station habitation modules 
3 plum brook station sandusky ohio 334 years this 
subsidiary to lewis research center is for the most part inactive 
but hypersonic aeronautical research facilities are being 
reactivated 
4 tie between lewis research center cleveland 393 years and 
stennis space center bay st louis miss 242 years lewis is 
the lead center for aeronautic propulsion research and technology 
and is developing space station power systems stennis tests the 
shuttles large propulsion systems 
5 tie between goddard space flight center greenbelt md 261 
years and wallops flight facility wallops island va 377 
years goddard manages earthrelated space science projects and 
controls hubble space telescope wallops a subsidiary of goddard 
directs sounding rocket program for earth observations 
6 ames research center mountain view calif 353 years 
conducts aeronautic and scientific research involving new 
technology 
7 kennedy space center cape canaveral fla 236 years 
directs shuttle launch operations 
8 langley research center hampton va 381 years conducts 
