the 265th quartermaster detachment of the south 
carolina national guard is one of the reserve units called up for 
possible duty in saudi arabia national writer fred bayles is 
following the 14 guardsmen as they prepare for deployment overseas 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
spc curtis young is usually the quiet 
one of the 256th but this night riding to the gym he blurts out 
im beginning to believe i made a mistake here 
my mommas got other boys and none of them was interested in 
the military he said and here i am and look where theyre 
sending me 
young a 25yearold prison guard is going to the mideast along 
with 14 fellow members of the 265th quartermaster detachment a 
water purification unit of the south carolina national guard 
he is not the only one a little disconcerted about his situation 
no one among this group of friends and neighbors from allendale 
sc is happy about going to a potential war zone there is no 
strutting or bravado about the subject there is hardly any talk 
about iraq or saddam hussein or the geopolitical issues the 
parttime soldiers are caught up in 
they make bad jokes about being gassed they laugh about the 
combinations of bad timing and fate that have put them in the 
situation but there is surprisingly little complaining 
