a cuban exile who had been a fugitive for 12 
years has pleaded guilty to conspiring to murder former chilean 
ambassador orlando letelier by helping bomb the exdiplomats car 
jose dionisio suarez esquivel a member of the cuban nationalist 
movement admitted in federal court monday that he gave a blasting 
cap to former chilean intelligence agent michael v townley who 
pleaded guilty to building the bomb that killed letelier and an 
associate on sept 21 1976 
letelier an outspoken critic of the rightwing military 
government of gen augusto pinochet and the associate ronni 
moffitt died after the bomb exploded beneath leteliers car on 
embassy row 
letelier had been his countrys ambassador to washington from 
1971 to 1973 he also served briefly as foreign minister in the 
leftist government of president salvador allende who died in a 
bloody military coup that overthrew his government in 1973 
two top military officials including the head of the chilean 
intelligence agency dina have been charged with participating in 
the murder but the chilean government which returned to civilian 
control earlier this year has refused to extradite the officials 
pinochet remains head of the chilean army and military courts 
retain jurisdiction over the two officials gen juan manuel 
contreras sepulveda and retired lt col pedro espinoza bravo the 
former head of dina 
under the deal approved by us district judge aubrey e 
robinson jr suarez 51 who was arrested april 11 in st 
petersburg fla cannot be sentenced to more than 12 years in 
prison even though the charge to which he pleaded guilty carries a 
maximum life sentence 
prosecutors also agreed not to prosecute his wife elizabeth 
gongora suarez for concealing a fugitive from authorities 
suarez also admitted that he townley and others went to 
leteliers residence two days before the bombing knowing that 
townley was to place an explosive device on the former diplomats 
car 
townley an americanborn dina agent pleaded guilty in 1978 to 
building the bomb and putting it beneath leteliers car he served 
a 40month prison term and has cooperated with the governments 
investigation 
