<TEXT>
the us military is training more 
personnel to work in chemical decontamination wards at field 
hospitals which would likely be overwhelmed if iraq were to 
unleash a major poison gas attack 
the training taking place in at least one major us base camp 
in saudi arabia comes as doctors and others who work in the 
decontamination units question their ability to handle a steady 
patient load over a lengthy period 
americans also are training saudis in how to decontaminate 
people who come in contact with chemicals at one base such 
training is being conducted every other day with groups of 10 to 12 
saudis from military medical facilities 
