weapons for years the saudis were really unprepared one air 
force officer involved in the training said 
most commanders discount the likelihood of any iraqi attack and 
have expressed confidence that their forces could intercept any 
missiles or planes carrying chemical weapons into saudi territory 
but as a precaution the united states has set up a series of 
field hospitals each with a separate area for decontaminating 
troops who come under chemical attack 
iraq has a large stock of chemical and nerve agents western 
intelligence sources have said 
saddam hussein boasted in april that iraq has developed binary 
weapons warheads or shells in which two chemical agents are housed 
in separate compartments these mingle on impact to form deadly 
gases 
the iraqis used chemical weapons mainly mustard gas and 
blister agents against iranian troops during their eightyear 
war which ended in ceasefire in 1988 
these did not prove especially effective western analysts 
believe that in military terms the casualties were low less than 
300 killed and possibly 20000 injured 
however the gas attacks had a considerable impact on iranian 
morale forcing infantrymen to wear the heavy protective suits and 
gas masks and thus reducing their fighting efficiency by about 
onethird 
most of the us field hospitals in saudi arabia have permanent 
staffs of about 20 people with a goal of treating 30 casualties an 
hour provided two thirds of the patients are walkins 
its a bit optimistic in this weather capt james t 
walker an air force doctor in charge of one of the field units 
said of the treatment targets 
walker said the units likely would need additional personnel in 
the event of heavy casualties because the treatment staff would 
have to work in bulky protective clothing and wear gas masks a 
problem in the sweltering saudi temperatures 
we will need to rotate people because its quite strenuous 
he said 
