theocracy 
before iraqs takeover of kuwait iranian foreign exchange 
earnings desperately needed to revive its moribund economy were 
expected to fall short by at least onethird of the 17 billion 
needed in 1990 according to western estimates 
but this was revised sharply upward after the price of oil 
irans principal export item soared following the iraqi invasion 
experts now say revenues could reach 19 billion this year 
that would strengthen rafsanjanis hand against irans radicals 
his political rivals who are bitterly opposed to his reforms and 
efforts to reestablish ties with the west 
