the tests be approved 
the experiments still must be approved by the food and drug 
administration before they can begin 
in the trials patients would be treated with cells that had 
been altered by the addition of new genes 
genes which direct the actions of cells will cause the treated 
cells to produce special proteins that will either amplify a 
biological action or replace proteins that were missing 
in the protocol for treatment of severe combined immune 
deficiency disease a human gene that instructs a cell to make 
adenosine deaminase or ada would be inserted into the patients 
white blood cells the disease is caused by a deficiency of ada 
the other experiments would involve patients with melanoma a 
gene for the cancerkilling tumor necrosis factor would be inserted 
into a patients tumor infiltrating lymphocytes which are 
cancerkilling white cells 
