business 
columbias astronomy mission with a 150 million observatory 
called astro has been delayed twice by hydrogen leaks and once by 
problems with a telescope aboard the shuttle the latest scrub 
occurred last week after hydrogen flooded the aft compartment 
nasa installed a new set of recirculation pumps monday and 
planned to test them late tuesday and early wednesday by flushing 
helium through the system 
in the pumps that were removed earlier helium tests failed to 
find any leaks said nasa spokesman george diller officials 
