launches because of range safety requirements 
also looming over nasas flight plans is the need to launch 
discovery between oct 5 and oct 23 with a satellite that will 
explore the suns polar regions 
if nasa misses that deadline discoverys 750 million mission 
will have to be postponed until late 1991 when earth is aligned 
properly again with the sun and jupiter 
the satellite called ulysses will use jupiters gravity to be 
whipped into the proper orbit around the sun it will be the first 
spacecraft to circle over the suns poles 
preparations for discoverys flight have been running several 
days behind because of a leak in the shuttles cooling system but 
launch managers are juggling the work schedule to make up for the 
lost time 
the problem has been traced to a vent in an ammonia boiler and 
mission managers have recommended that discovery fly with the leaky 
boiler as long as the leak remains small given the amount of 
leakage about 1 percent a day there would be more than enough 
coolant to last the fourday flight diller said the boiler is 
needed to cool the shuttle during landings 
