<TEXT>
a federal judge tuesday denied a motion by 
convicted spy jonathan j pollard to withdraw his 1986 guilty plea 
to selling a wide range of defense secrets to israel 
us district judge aubrey e robinson jr also rejected 
allegations by harvard university law professor alan dershowitz 
that federal prosecutors improperly supplied the judge with 
information that influenced the decision to impose a life sentence 
on the former civilian navy intelligence analyst 
dershowitz based his allegation on a conversation he says he had 
last fall with former supreme court justice arthur goldberg who 
died jan 19 at the age of 81 according to court papers unsealed 
tuesday by robinson 
dershowitz said in an affidavit that goldberg told him of a 
conversation with robinson in which the judge explained why he gave 
pollard a life sentence 
goldberg quoted robinson as saying that information from 
prosecutors that pollard had sold israel us spy satellite photos 
of tests of israelimade missiles in south africa weighed 
heavily in the decision to impose a life sentence according to 
the affidavit 
in his opinion robinson denied receiving the information which 
he said was false and added that the claim of improper contact by 
prosecutors is based upon pure hearsay twice over 
the judge rejected a defense request that he retire from the 
case 
pollard received a life sentence in 1987 for his guilty plea to 
conspiracy to commit espionage 
at sentencing prosecutors said that pollard had given israel 
enough classified documents to fill a large closet 
in his motions pollard claimed that prosecutors reneged on 
their promise not to seek life sentence by framing their 
presentence arguments to ensure that robinson imposed the life 
term anyway 
prosecutors denied in court papers that they improperly gave 
robinson any information about pollards spying that was not 
produced during the trial 
the government noted that the testing of the israeli jericho 
missiles in south africa did not occur until july 1989 and 
hardly could have formed the basis of a sentencing decision made in 
1987 
we think it more likely that assuming that there was some 
conversation between chief judge robinson and justice goldberg 
that they discussed current events and that their conversation has 
been distorted in the retelling said a government brief 
dershowitz who served as one of goldbergs law clerks in the 
1960s quoted the former justice as saying that he thought that 
because robinson is black he would be particularly sensitive 
to evidence of an israelisouth african connection 
robinson did not specifically say whether he ever talked with 
goldberg about the case except to say the courts recollection 
of events is in stark contradition to that claim 
prosecutors dryly noted in their pleadings that it was 
convenient for dershowitz to claim he received information from 
someone now deceased 
this argument prompted pollards defense attorney hamilton p 
fox iii to file a separate affidavit stating that dershowitz 
contacted him almost two months before goldbergs death to relate 
the details of the conversation 
goldberg was appointed to the supreme court by president kennedy 
but resigned from the high court when president johnson named him 
ambassador to the united nations 
