his intention to step down from his post at the 21nation 
organization which is deeply torn by divisions over the gulf 
crisis 
the groups un envoy clovis maksoud appealed tuesday that 
the wound inflicted on kuwait not lead to amputation of part 
of the arab body politic 
maksoud told a news conference he can longer no longer reconcile 
his own convictions in favor of a larger arab role with arab 
acceptance of the buildup of us and foreign forces in the gulf 
he complained that arab nations were losing credibility because 
of their failure to act together he said they were becoming 
marginalized because the united states not an arab front was 
resisting iraqs occupation of kuwait 
he said arabs must seek a third way between accepting iraqi 
domination of kuwait and allowing the us military buildup 
hundreds of thousands of us and iraqi troops are poised on 
opposite sides of the kuwaitisaudi border in a standoff 
maksoud said he favored breathing space to permit an arab 
solution to what he called an arab problem including a significant 
arab military force to replace the usled military operation 
in his comments maksoud also said the gulf crisis should not 
deflect arab states from their fundamental aim of reaching a just 
settlement with israel 
