iraq 
the resolution was passed just hours before president bush was 
appearing before a joint house and senate session to report on the 
crisis triggered by saddams invasion and occupation of neighboring 
kuwait 
it is the sense of the senate that in the event of hostilities 
between the united states and the government of iraq it shall be 
the policy of the united states to pursue saddam hussein and other 
such perpetrators as may be determined responsible in order to 
bring them to justice as war criminals it said 
