<TEXT>
the heaviest singleday rainfall in 70 
years drenched south korea on tuesday killing at least 45 people 
and forcing more than 350000 to flee their homes 
president roh taewoo said relief efforts were like fighting a 
war 
the seoul area was swamped by 15 inches of rain in 24 hours the 
most rain fell at suwon just south of seoul which had 168 
inches the main disaster relief center said 
a 100yard section of the han rivers bank just west of seoul 
burst overnight sending tons of water into a farming area of rice 
paddies and villages officials said the 300000 residents were 
being evacuated 
no amount of words can describe this situation said police 
lt kim sungho from the scene its hellish 
thousands of people were stranded on rooftops and thousands 
were ferried to higher ground 
official figures said 45 people were known dead 31 missing and 
66000 homeless however the figures did not take into account the 
new flooding from the han or the evacuations there 
the central disaster relief center said the rainfall was the 
heaviest in the country in a single day in 70 years property 
damage was initially estimated at 25 million 
the airfield at the 7th us air force headquarters south of 
seoul was flooded and f16 jet fighters were sandbagged about two 
dozen koreans in makeshift boats floated over a submerged fence and 
onto the flooded runways and had to be rescued a spokesman said 
us and south korean military helicopters and large army trucks 
evacuated children and shopkeepers stranded on tops of houses and 
buildings 
one hospital on the outskirts of seoul evacuated its patients 
and witnesses reported seeing patients wading through waisthigh 
water with belongings held over their heads 
this is the worst weather disaster in memory roh said after 
briefings at the han river flood control center protecting 
people from this rain is like fighting a war 
korean soldiers used rubber dinghies to rescue people stranded 
in lowlying areas around olympic park the olympic expressway was 
flooded and nearby riverside park areas were submerged 
a buddhist temple was buried in a mudslide with five monks 
inside news reports said 
the national news agency yonhap said the dead included a 
9yearold girl swept away by flood waters and a 3yearold 
sleeping in her home 
in the port of inchon west of seoul nine homes were buried in a 
landslide and 20 people were missing police said more than 15000 
chickens drowned at a chicken farm 
