up the soviet union through his policies of glasnost 
enrollment in undergraduate russian classes has risen 40 percent 
the last three years at the university of california at los 
angeles center for russian and east european studies considered a 
gauge of collegiate interest nationwide in those languages 
chinese was the second fastestgrowing foreign language behind 
japanese in secondary schools from 1983 through 1986 the last 
period for which statistics were compiled by the modern language 
association it grew 28 percent during that span to 3400 students 
and continues to surge experts say 
you cant ignore a language spoken by onefifth of the human 
population and consider yourself to be part of the world said 
norman colb schools superintendent in mamaroneck ny the new 
york city suburb has one of 40 us schools with a grant to teach 
chinese 
spanish remains the most widely taught foreign language at the 
college level followed by french which it surpassed in 1970 then 
come german italian russian latin and japanese 
now were constantly bombarded with other languages because of 
satellites cable tv and increased foreign travel said 
stansfield of the washington linguistics center we can no longer 
demand that our international business be done in english 
the percentage of high school students studying foreign 
languages is now just below the alltime peak year of 1934 when 
more than a third of secondary students were in language courses 
but other developed countries require more of their students 
the japanese have made a great effort to learn english 
requiring it be taught from elementary school on stansfield said 
foreign language study is mandatory in continental europe starting 
in seventh grade secondary school requirements in britain also are 
tougher than in the united states 
