surtsey like iceland itself is a piece 
of the midatlantic ridge 
extending from greenland to antarctica the ridge is the earths 
largest geological feature it was formed when continentsized 
plates of the earths crust started to separate allowing molten 
magma to well up in between 
the ancient icelandic parliament site of thingvellir east of 
reykjavik lies astride the gap between the north american and 
eurasian plates 
you can see north america on one side and right next to you 
eurasia said kathleen crane of the lamontdoherty geological 
observatory in palisades ny who has done research on surtsey 
