tried to find a buyer for the junk bonds despite the fact that the 
thrift is insolvent 
columbia was 350 million in the red according to the latest 
report largely due to the declining value of the junk bond 
portfolio but also because of recent real estate losses 
in late july columbia agreed to sell the bonds for 3 billion 
to a partnership assembled by gordon investment corp a merchant 
bank based in new york and toronto a principal of gordon 
investment is hong kong billionaire entrepreneur li kashing who 
could not be reached for comment 
