million down and given columbia a 10year note for the remaining 
27 billion at an interest rate of 105 percent 
if the value of the bonds fell 10 percent below the purchase 
price the buyers could have walked away from the deal losing 
their down payment but avoiding further losses 
in that case the junk bonds would have wound up back in the 
hands of columbia and if the thrift were seized of the 
taxpayers 
in its announcement the ots said the proposed 10year 
