more than 330 million as more than 6 million cases of fruit in the 
united states were destroyed 
the association said research at the university of california at 
davis showed that if the two grapes had been contaminated with 
cyanide other grapes in the same case also would have contained 
the poison however none was found the fda has said 
the studies also showed that because cyanide was found at such 
high levels it would have to have been introduced in the grapes 
more recently than two weeks before when the ship was in chile 
