banking executives shrugged off a barrage of 
negative reports on their industry tuesday pronouncing the 
business sound but adding that it could be in better shape if 
congress relaxes restrictions on the kinds of products the banks 
can sell 
the commercial banking industry is healthy strong enough to 
weather a tougher economic climate in the 1990s said michael p 
