youre dealing with some very fundamental things here auto 
analyst joseph phillippi of shearson lehman brothers said tuesday 
in past years including 1984 negotiating arguments centered on 
a percent or two in wages or on how financial guarantees for 
laidoff workers would work 
these days the issues and especially their potential effects 
are much deeper and according to phillippi its mostly due to the 
growth of the us manufacturing base by japanese automakers 
