big three at the time the automakers were in the financial dumps 
as the final minutes ticked off of the bargaining clock in 1984 
the uaw leadership couldnt hold its membership workers began 
walking off their jobs before the midnight deadline 
by the time uaw president owen bieber announced a strike at 12 
gm assembly plants and its technical center in warren mich 
employees already were walking picket lines 
the following day not enough workers showed up at their jobs at 
gms lordstown ohio assembly plant which was not officially 
struck and that factory shut down 
the strike lasted for seven days and the union bragged that it 
had won major guarantees on job security and important wage and 
benefit gains three years later the union said it built on the 
job security provisions of 1984 
but since 1987 gm has closed four assembly plants putting 
about 9000 uaw members on layoff 
